# Dataset

The dataset contains transactional sales information including:

- Date
- Day	
- Month	
- Year	
- Customer_Age	
- Age_Group	
- Customer_Gender	
- Country	State	
- Product_Category	
- Sub_Category	
- Product	
- Order_Quantity	
- Unit_Cost	
- Unit_Price	
- Profit
- Cost	
- Revenue

---

## 1. Total Revenue

### Business Question

How much total revenue has the company generated?

### SQL Query

SELECT SUM(Revenue) AS Total_Revenue
FROM sales_analysis;

## 2. Total Profit

### Business Question

How much total profit has been earned?

### SQL Query

SELECT SUM(Profit) AS Total_Profit
FROM sales_analysis;

## 3. Top 10 Products

### Business Question

Which products generate the highest sales?

### SQL Query

SELECT Product,
SUM(Revenue) AS Revenue
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Product
ORDER BY Revenue DESC
LIMIT 10;


## 4. Revenue by Category

### Business Question

Which product categories contribute the highest revenue?

### SQL Query

SELECT Product_Category,
SUM(Revenue) Revenue
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Product_Category;

## 5. Revenue by Country

### Business Question

Which countries contribute the highest revenue?

### SQL Query

SELECT Country,
SUM(Revenue) Revenue
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Country
ORDER BY Revenue DESC;

## 6. Sales by Month

### Business Question

How do monthly sales change over time?

### SQL Query

SELECT Month,
SUM(Revenue) Revenue
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Month;

## 7. Gender-wise Sales

### Business Question

Which gender contributes more revenue?

### SQL Query

SELECT Customer_Gender,
SUM(Revenue) Revenue
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Customer_Gender;


## 8. Age Group Analysis

### Business Question

Which age group spends the most?

### SQL Query

SELECT Age_Group,
SUM(Revenue) Revenue,
SUM(Profit) Profit
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Age_Group;


## 9. Most Profitable Product

### Business Question

Which product generates the highest profit?

### SQL Query

SELECT Product,
SUM(Profit) Profit
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Product
ORDER BY Profit DESC
LIMIT 10;

## 10. Profit Margin

### Business Question

What percentage of revenue becomes profit?

### SQL Query

SELECT Product,
SUM(Profit)/SUM(Revenue)*100 AS Profit_Margin
FROM sales_analysis
GROUP BY Product;
